# Goal: Task Priority System

## Desired End State

Users can assign priority levels (high, medium, low) to tasks, see visual priority indicators at a glance, and filter their task list by priority to focus on what matters most.

## Key Outcomes

- Every task has a priority (default: medium)
- Priority is visually obvious without clicking into a task
- Users can change priority with minimal friction
- Users can filter to see only high-priority items when focused

## Non-Goals

- No priority-based notifications or reminders
- No automatic priority assignment based on due dates
- No priority inheritance for subtasks

## Context

- This is a web app built with Next.js and a SQL database
- There's an existing task list UI with card-based layout
- The database already has a tasks table but no priority column
